    <definition>
      <title>The Vertex Form of a Quadratic</title>
      <p>
	The <term>vertex form of a quadratic</term> equation <m>f(x) = ax^2 + bx + c</m> is
	<me>f(x) = a(x - h)^2 + k</me>
	where <m>(h,k)</m> is the vertex of the parabola.
      </p>
    </definition>
